<abstract><t>This document describes a general framework called CoDel (Controlled Delay) that controls bufferbloat-generated excess delay in modern networking environments.  CoDel consists of an estimator, a setpoint, and a control loop.  It requires no configuration in normal Internet deployments.</t></abstract>

